Title: Config files and plugins for Vi improved
Author: cyberbrain
Date: 12.09.2013

I)   Introduction
    This is my vim configuration repository. It primary goal is
    to provide IDE for easy and fast development. It is used and
    tested for PHP and Python projects and works well. Everything
    else you need you can install via pathogen. :P

II)  Instalation
    Clone this directory to your ~/.vim directory. Then map vimrc
    to your home dir so config is invoked on vim startup.

III) Content:
     -syntax                - Syntax highlight (Auto)
     -airline               - Tabs for buffers
     -surround              - Parentheses, brackets, quotes, XML tags
     -folds                 - Folding (check fold method) (za,zf,zd...)
     -snippets              - Define your snippets in ~/.vim/after/snippets/
     -ctags                 - Jump to definition of class or method (Ctrl+], Ctrl+t)
     -themes                - Monokai, HappyHacking...
